{
  "doc_id": "43892",
  "text": "Despite the high mortality rate for bartonellosis in Peru, studies on Bartonella pathogens are insufficient and mainly focused on B. bacilliformis [CITATION_1] . We previously reported identification of non-bacilliformis Bartonella in Peru during a clinical treatment trial [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Using single-locus sequence typing, we identified 3 isolates (designated 20.00, 20.60, and 41.60) from 4 whole blood specimens collected from 2 patients (nos. 20 and 41) at day 0 or 60 during the clinical treatment trial in the Ancash region of Peru and found that these isolates had citrate synthase (gltA) gene sequences that diverged from that of B. bacilliformis reference strain KC583 [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] . Multilocus sequencing typing and microbiological analyses indicated these 3 isolates are members of a novel Bartonella species, subsequently name B. ancashensis [CITATION_8] .",
